translated:
Lagerquist, Gunnar Harald Hilding, parish priest, Gullaboby, b. 25/2/81 in Gärdslösa, Kalmar 1st, son of vicar Gustaf L. and Ida Runkrantz. Married to Elsa Nordstén since 13. Children: Alvar b. 15, Bertil b. 18, Gustaf b. 25. Obtained a master's degree in divinity in Kalmar in 01, a bachelor's degree in theology in Lund in 02, a master's degree in theology and practical theological exam in 08, ordained as a priest in Kalmar in 09. Has served as an assistant vicar in Söder-åkra and Madesjö, acting pastor in Torslun-da and assistant curate in Algutsrum, acting curate in Algutsrum and simultaneously acting pastor in Glömminge from 12-15, acting pastor in Norra Möckleby from 13-15, vacant parish vicar there from 15-21, assistant pastor in Sandby from 18-21, parish priest in Gullabo since 21. Also served as a singing teacher at Lund's private elementary school from 03-08 and as a teacher at Öland's folk high school in Skogsby from 10-12 and 15-21. Delegate of the Diaconal Board from 16-21, delegate of the National Antiquities Board in 46, member of the Swedish Society of Letters, History, and Antiquities from 09-16. Author of poems, articles, and sermons in newspapers and magazines. Received State Travel Stipend in 13. Awarded Litteris et Artibus in 46, Swedish Red Cross merits, Mannerheim Medal in 47. 

*Lagerwik, Elsa Hansen, dentist, Tranås, b. 5/10/96 in Norway, daughter of merchant Axel Hansson and Alma Nilsson. Completed studies at WalHnska school in Stockholm in 15, completed dental studies in 20, became a dentist in 22. Has been practicing in Tranås since 22.
